<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,1085,1685]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,379,1517,1542]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">DISCUSSION:</emphasis>
Raušer (1968) first described the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[829,966,1518,1541]" class="Insecta" family="Capniidae" genus="Mesocapnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[829,966,1518,1541]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Mesocapnia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on this species which is endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[151,263,1553,1577]" name="Mongolia" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
. Our collections near the 
<typeStatus box="[559,607,1554,1578]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">type</typeStatus>
locality only documented 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Klapalek" baseAuthorityYear="1920" box="[913,1060,1553,1577]" class="Insecta" family="Capniidae" genus="Mesocapnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis box="[913,1060,1553,1577]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. variabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in that region but we need more extensive collecting to confirm presence, particularly near 
<collectingRegion box="[819,967,1589,1613]" country="Mongolia" name="Ulaanbaatar" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Ulaan Baatar</collectingRegion>
in Bogd Khan and the headwaters of the Terelj River. Evaluation of the original 
<typeStatus box="[607,655,1626,1650]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">type</typeStatus>
specimens and collecting earlier in the year at the 
<typeStatus box="[1250,1298,1626,1650]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">type</typeStatus>
locality are needed to confirm the validity of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
